Description: Fragment of oval/rectangular handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine purplish brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Helios herm symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 28a, 14. Name Menandros. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0733; Athenian Agora SS8602, unpublished, is also from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1210)
